OL,3,CTrain driver minimum age to be lowered
OL,4,Cto 18 from June
OL,6,FEighteen-year-olds will be allowed to
OL,7,Fdrive trains from June 30, the
OL,8,FDepartment for Transport (DfT) has
OL,9,Fannounced after concerns about the
OL,10,Fnumber of drivers approaching
OL,11,Fretirement.
OL,13,FThe current minimum age for driving
OL,14,Ftrains is 20, but the new legislation
OL,15,Fwill be brought before parliament on
OL,16,FTuesday to coincide with National
OL,17,FApprenticeship Week.
OL,19,FThe DfT said a quarter of train
OL,20,Fdrivers are expected to reach
OL,21,Fretirement age by 2030.
